Dennis Naku, Port Harcourt THE Rivers State Government said more than 107,000 persons have been tested for COVID-19 free of charge in the state since the outbreak of the pandemic. The state Commissioner for Health, Prof. Princewill Chike, gave the figure during the bidding for the rehabilitation and refurbishment of 105-bed Kelsey Harrison Hospital and the Dental Maxilo Facial Hospital both in Port Harcourt, the state capital. Chike maintained that contrary to the belief by some persons, COVID-19 was not a hoax and urged members of the public not to live in denial. “The Rivers State Government has tested over 107, 000 samples. To be precise, the government has tested over 107,150 samples for COVID-19 free of charge. “Of course, you know the cost of each sample. It is between N50,000 and N60,000 for a government to do that. So, that will tell you how much money has been committed. We thank God for the Governor of Rivers State for his commitment. “Every adult in this part of the world should help us protect the vulnerable. We are starting on that note because it is important,” the commissioner stated. Chike disclosed move by the State Governor, Nyesom Wike, to rehabilitate moribund medical facilities in the state and added that it was part of the promises the government had placed on health services. According to Chike, “His Excellency has done very well in the health sector. For him to say let us rehabilitate, refurbish and put in use the Professor Kelsey Harrison Specialist Hospital and the Dental and Maxilo Facial Hospital means that the best is yet to come. New buildings are also going to come up at the dental and Maxilo Facial Hospital.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com